{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:40.625756+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 72788d2a989f3940789f0da9ef7edb9fe02028cf)", "id": "lc_bdd90ba0-302c-4610-a12c-bfc86c6dae18"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import vue from '@vitejs/plugin-vue'\nimport { resolve } from 'path'\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vite'\nimport { createHtmlPlugin } from 'vite-plugin-html'\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  plugins: [\n    vue(),\n    createHtmlPlugin({\n      minify: true,\n      inject: {\n        data: {\n          title: 'ProjectName',\n          description: 'A single page application created using Vue.js 3',\n        },\n      },\n    }),\n  ],\n  resolve: {\n    alias: {\n      '@': resolve(__dirname, '/src'),\n      '~bootstrap': 'bootstrap',\n    },\n  },\n  css: {\n    preprocessorOptions: {\n      scss: {\n        additionalData: `@use \"@/scss/variables\" as *;`,\n        // https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/40962#issuecomment-2448214806\n        silenceDeprecations: ['color-functions', 'global-builtin', 'import'],\n      },\n    },\n  },\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    globalSetup: './tests/vitest.global-setup.js',\n    setupFiles: ['./tests/vitest.globals.js'],\n    environment: 'jsdom',\n    reporters: ['default'],\n    coverage: {\n      reporter: ['text', 'json'],\n    },\n  },\n})\n", "id": "lc_e099f884-e7f2-461d-a716-57cd0d52ca02"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "96bdf2cd-fda5-4393-a268-775795693ee3", "tool_call_id": "call_00_FLWMooZ6B4NQZ25mo4D89268", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:56.480420+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here’s the full explanation of how the app bootstraps, handles routing/layout, and loads the About page.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Entry Point\n\n`index.html` contains `<div id=\"app\"></div>` and a module script pointing to `src/main.js`. Vite’s HTML plugin injects the `<title>` and `<meta name=\"description\">` from the config.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Vue App Initialisation (`src/main.js`)\n\n```js\nimport { createPinia } from 'pinia'\nimport { createApp } from 'vue'\nimport Default from '@/layouts/default/Default.vue'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport { router } from './router'\n\nconst app = createApp(App)\n\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // register the default layout globally\napp.use(createPinia())                    // state management\napp.use(router)                           // install Vue Router\n\napp.mount('#app')\n```\n\n- The root component `App.vue` is mounted.\n- **`LayoutDefault` is registered globally** so that `<component :is=\"layout\">` can resolve to it.\n- Pinia (state management) and Vue Router are installed.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Dynamic Layout Resolution in `App.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nimport '@/scss/app.scss'\n\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\n- The computed property `layout` reads `this.$route.meta.layout` (defaulting to `'default'`).\n- It returns the string `'layout-default'`, which matches the globally registered component **`LayoutDefault`**.\n- The `<component :is=\"layout\">` dynamically renders the correct layout wrapper, which in turn contains `<RouterView />` for the page content.\n- Global SCSS is imported once here via `@/scss/app.scss`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Router Configuration (`src/router/index.js`)\n\n```js\nimport { createRouter, createWebHashHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    // route level code-splitting\n    component: () => import(/* webpackChunkName: \"about\" */ '../views/About.vue'),\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\nconst router = createRouter({\n  linkActiveClass: 'active',\n  history,\n  routes,\n})\nexport { router }\n```\n\n- **Hash history** (`createWebHashHistory`) is used.\n- Two routes:\n  - `/` → eagerly loaded `Home.vue`\n  - `/about` → **lazy‑loaded** via dynamic `import()`, creating a separate chunk named `about.[hash].js`.\n- Both routes set `meta: { layout: 'default' }`, which `App.vue` reads to select the layout.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Default Layout (`src/layouts/default/Default.vue`)\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n- Renders a **navigation bar** (`DefaultNav.vue`) at the top.\n- A `<slot />` where the routed page content (from `<RouterView>`) is injected.\n- A **footer** (`DefaultFooter.vue`) at the bottom.\n- The layout uses Bootstrap 5 classes and a sticky footer pattern.\n\nThe navigation bar (`DefaultNav.vue`) contains `<RouterLink to=\"/\">Home</RouterLink>` and `<RouterLink to=\"/about\">About</RouterLink>`, enabling client‑side navigation without a full page reload.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How the About Page Is Loaded\n\n1. The user clicks the **About** link (a `<RouterLink to=\"/about\">`).\n2. Vue Router intercepts the navigation to `/about`.\n3. Router looks up the route definition; it has `meta: { layout: 'default' }` and a **lazy‑loaded component** (`() => import('../views/About.vue')`).\n4. **Code‑splitting kicks in**: the browser fetches the separate chunk `about.[hash].js` (created by Vite at build time).\n5. Once the chunk loads, Vue Router renders the `About.vue` component.\n6. `App.vue` reads `$route.meta.layout` → `'default'` → resolves `<component :is=\"layout-default\">`, which is the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component.\n7. The layout renders `DefaultNav`, then `<slot />` (where `<RouterView>` outputs the `About.vue` template), then `DefaultFooter`.\n8. The About page content is simply:\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary Flow\n\n```\nindex.html\n  └─ src/main.js\n       ├─ createApp(App)\n       ├─ register global LayoutDefault component\n       ├─ install Pinia\n       ├─ install router\n       └─ mount('#app')\n\nApp.vue\n  └─ reads $route.meta.layout → 'default'\n  └─ renders <component :is=\"LayoutDefault\">\n         ├─ DefaultNav (router-links: Home, About)\n         ├─ <RouterView /> (dynamic page content)\n         └─ DefaultFooter\n\nWhen navigating to /about:\n  1. Router triggers dynamic import() of About.vue\n  2. Browser downloads about.[hash].js chunk\n  3. Router renders About.vue inside RouterView\n  4. Same layout wraps it (DefaultNav + slot + DefaultFooter)\n```", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1610, "prompt_tokens": 9513, "total_tokens": 11123, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 301, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 8576}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 8576, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 937}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "1ad9f76b-b75d-48f7-9e53-621ec840d16d", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea774-f572-7c70-b3da-528355098689-0", "too